Scanzy
Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy explains how Scanzy ("we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects information that you provide to us when you use our app, or visit our website
https://www.scanzy.com
.
Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information from you:
Personal information, such as your name, email address, and telephone number, when you voluntarily provide it to us through forms, surveys, or other interactive features on our website.
Technical information, such as your IP address, browser type and version, and the pages you visit on our website, collected automatically as you navigate through our website.
Cookies, small data files that are placed on your device or computer and often include an anonymous unique identifier. For more information about cookies, and how to disable them, please see our Cookies Policy.
How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect from you in the following ways:
To provide you with information or services that you request from us.
To improve the content and functionality of our website.
To communicate with you about our products, services, and promotions.
To analyze and understand how our website is used.
Sharing Your Information
We may share your information with third parties for the following purposes:
To comply with legal obligations, such as responding to a subpoena or court order.
To protect the rights, property, or safety of Scanzy, our customers, or others.
To provide information or services that you request from us.
To perform services on our behalf, such as data analysis, and payment processing.
We may also share your information with our affiliates, subsidiaries, or parent companies, but only for the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy.
Your Rights
Under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), you have certain rights in relation to your personal information, including:
The right to access your personal information,
The right to rectify any inaccuracies in your personal information,
The right to request that we delete your personal information,
The right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal information,
The right to object to the processing of your personal information, and
The right to data portability.
You also have the right to opt-out of receiving marketing communications from us at any time.
Security of Your Information
We take the security of your information very seriously and have implemented appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your information from unauthorized access, use, disclosure, or destruction.
Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may make changes to this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make any changes, we will update the "Last Updated" date at the top of this Privacy Policy. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting the information we collect.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us by email at
admin@scanzy.com
or by phone at 855-941-0303.
This Privacy Policy was last updated on January 13, 2023.
By using our website, you consent to our collection, use, and sharing of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
